   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Multi-Purpose Cash Assistance to Vulnerable Households in Tonga</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving multi-purpose cash assistance to vulnerable communities affected by the volcano eruption and subsequent tsunami. This IOM project provides humanitarian assistance to people through registration and cash distribution. The project provides life-saving assistance to 4,900 people, including 1,500 women, 1,000 men, 2,400 children, and 735 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
